    <p style="color:#333">The martial arts school management software landscape has evolved significantly over the past few years. Platforms have become more specialized, pricing models have shifted, and school owners now have more options than ever. The challenge is no longer finding software that works, it is finding the one that works best for your specific school.</p>

    <p style="color:#333">We evaluated the top eight platforms used by martial arts schools in 2026, looking at features, pricing, ease of use, customer support, and how well each platform serves the unique needs of martial arts businesses. Here is what we found.</p>

    <h2 style="font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif">What We Evaluated</h2>

    <p style="color:#333">Each platform was assessed across six categories:</p>

    <ul style="color:#333;line-height:1.8">
      <li><strong>Martial arts-specific features:</strong> Belt tracking, rank management, program-based scheduling, trial management</li>
      <li><strong>Billing and payments:</strong> Automated billing, failed payment recovery, flexible membership options, processing fees</li>
      <li><strong>Ease of use:</strong> Interface design, learning curve, mobile experience for both staff and students</li>
      <li><strong>Reporting and analytics:</strong> Dashboard quality, available reports, data export options</li>
      <li><strong>Customer support:</strong> Responsiveness, availability, onboarding assistance</li>
      <li><strong>Value for money:</strong> Feature-to-price ratio, transparent pricing, contract flexibility</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 style="font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif">1. Gripmode</h2>

    <p style="color:#333">Gripmode was built from the ground up specifically for martial arts schools, and that focus shows in every aspect of the platform. Unlike general fitness management tools that have been adapted for martial arts, Gripmode's core architecture is designed around the way martial arts schools actually operate: belt progressions, multi-program memberships, family accounts, and instructor-led class structures.</p>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Key strengths:</strong></p>
    <ul style="color:#333;line-height:1.8">
      <li>Purpose-built for martial arts with native belt and rank tracking</li>
      <li>Clean, modern interface with minimal learning curve</li>
      <li>Robust automated billing with intelligent failed payment recovery</li>
      <li>Real-time analytics dashboard designed for martial arts KPIs</li>
      <li>Built-in lead management and trial conversion tracking</li>
      <li>Coach payroll tools with per-class and commission calculations</li>
    </ul>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Considerations:</strong></p>
    <ul style="color:#333;line-height:1.8">
      <li>Newer platform, so the feature set is still expanding</li>
      <li>Best suited for martial arts-only schools rather than multi-sport facilities</li>
    </ul>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Pricing:</strong> Transparent, flat-rate pricing with no long-term contracts required. Competitive processing fees.</p>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Best for:</strong> Martial arts school owners who want a modern, purpose-built platform without the bloat of general fitness software.</p>

    <h2 style="font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif">2. Zen Planner</h2>

    <p style="color:#333">Zen Planner has been a staple in the martial arts and fitness industry for years. It offers a comprehensive feature set that covers most operational needs, from billing and scheduling to member management and reporting.</p>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Key strengths:</strong></p>
    <ul style="color:#333;line-height:1.8">
      <li>Established platform with a large user base</li>
      <li>Comprehensive feature set including website integration</li>
      <li>Strong billing and payment processing</li>
      <li>Good reporting capabilities</li>
    </ul>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Considerations:</strong></p>
    <ul style="color:#333;line-height:1.8">
      <li>Interface can feel dated compared to newer platforms</li>
      <li>Designed for general fitness businesses, so martial arts-specific features sometimes require workarounds</li>
      <li>Pricing has increased significantly over the years</li>
      <li>Some users report slow customer support response times</li>
    </ul>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Pricing:</strong> Tiered pricing based on active members. Entry-level plans start around $117/month.</p>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Best for:</strong> Established schools that need a proven, feature-rich platform and do not mind a steeper learning curve.</p>

    <h2 style="font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif">3. Kicksite</h2>

    <p style="color:#333">Kicksite positions itself as a martial arts-focused management platform with an emphasis on simplicity. It covers the basics well and is popular among smaller schools.</p>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Key strengths:</strong></p>
    <ul style="color:#333;line-height:1.8">
      <li>Built specifically for martial arts schools</li>
      <li>Simple, straightforward interface</li>
      <li>Good belt and rank tracking features</li>
      <li>Affordable pricing for smaller schools</li>
    </ul>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Considerations:</strong></p>
    <ul style="color:#333;line-height:1.8">
      <li>Limited advanced reporting and analytics</li>
      <li>Mobile experience could be stronger</li>
      <li>Fewer automation features compared to competitors</li>
      <li>Integration options are limited</li>
    </ul>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Pricing:</strong> Competitive pricing starting around $50-100/month depending on school size.</p>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Best for:</strong> Smaller martial arts schools that need the basics done well without a lot of complexity.</p>

    <h2 style="font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif">4. PushPress</h2>

    <p style="color:#333">PushPress originated in the CrossFit space but has expanded to serve a broader range of fitness businesses, including martial arts schools. It offers a modern interface and a unique freemium pricing model.</p>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Key strengths:</strong></p>
    <ul style="color:#333;line-height:1.8">
      <li>Modern, clean interface</li>
      <li>Free tier available for basic features</li>
      <li>Strong point-of-sale and retail features</li>
      <li>Good mobile app experience</li>
    </ul>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Considerations:</strong></p>
    <ul style="color:#333;line-height:1.8">
      <li>Not martial arts-specific; lacks native belt tracking</li>
      <li>Advanced features require paid tiers that can get expensive</li>
      <li>Reporting features are basic on lower tiers</li>
      <li>Payment processing fees can be higher than competitors</li>
    </ul>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Pricing:</strong> Free tier available. Paid plans start around $159/month. Higher processing fees on the free tier.</p>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Best for:</strong> Schools that also operate as general fitness facilities and want a modern platform with flexible pricing.</p>

    <h2 style="font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif">5. Spark Membership</h2>

    <p style="color:#333">Spark Membership is built for martial arts schools and offers a comprehensive feature set with a focus on marketing and lead generation tools.</p>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Key strengths:</strong></p>
    <ul style="color:#333;line-height:1.8">
      <li>Martial arts-focused with belt and attendance tracking</li>
      <li>Strong marketing and lead generation tools</li>
      <li>Built-in review and reputation management</li>
      <li>Family account support</li>
    </ul>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Considerations:</strong></p>
    <ul style="color:#333;line-height:1.8">
      <li>Interface is functional but not the most polished</li>
      <li>Can feel overwhelming due to the large number of features</li>
      <li>Pricing is not always transparent; requires a demo to get a quote</li>
      <li>Some features feel bolted on rather than natively integrated</li>
    </ul>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Pricing:</strong> Custom pricing based on school size and features selected. Typically requires a consultation.</p>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Best for:</strong> Schools that prioritize marketing and lead generation alongside operational management.</p>

    <h2 style="font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif">6. Wodify</h2>

    <p style="color:#333">Wodify started as a CrossFit-focused platform and has grown to serve various fitness business types. It offers strong performance tracking and community features.</p>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Key strengths:</strong></p>
    <ul style="color:#333;line-height:1.8">
      <li>Excellent performance tracking and workout logging</li>
      <li>Strong community and social features</li>
      <li>Good scheduling and class management</li>
      <li>Modern interface design</li>
    </ul>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Considerations:</strong></p>
    <ul style="color:#333;line-height:1.8">
      <li>Not designed for martial arts; no belt tracking</li>
      <li>Performance tracking features are oriented toward strength and conditioning</li>
      <li>Limited martial arts school community for peer support</li>
      <li>Pricing can escalate with add-ons</li>
    </ul>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Pricing:</strong> Plans start around $99/month with additional costs for premium features.</p>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Best for:</strong> Hybrid facilities that combine martial arts with CrossFit or strength training programs.</p>

    <h2 style="font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif">7. Mindbody</h2>

    <p style="color:#333">Mindbody is the largest platform in the fitness and wellness industry. It offers an enormous feature set and marketplace exposure but was designed primarily for yoga studios, spas, and general fitness businesses.</p>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Key strengths:</strong></p>
    <ul style="color:#333;line-height:1.8">
      <li>Massive marketplace with consumer discovery features</li>
      <li>Extensive integration ecosystem</li>
      <li>Comprehensive scheduling and booking capabilities</li>
      <li>Strong brand recognition</li>
    </ul>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Considerations:</strong></p>
    <ul style="color:#333;line-height:1.8">
      <li>Not martial arts-specific; significant workarounds needed</li>
      <li>One of the most expensive platforms on this list</li>
      <li>Complex interface with a steep learning curve</li>
      <li>Customer support quality varies widely based on your plan tier</li>
      <li>Contract terms can be inflexible</li>
    </ul>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Pricing:</strong> Plans range from approximately $139 to $699/month depending on features and location count.</p>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Best for:</strong> Large multi-service facilities that offer martial arts alongside yoga, personal training, and other modalities, and want marketplace exposure.</p>

    <h2 style="font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif">8. Glofox</h2>

    <p style="color:#333">Glofox is a gym and studio management platform that emphasizes branding and white-label mobile apps. It has gained traction among boutique fitness studios and some martial arts schools.</p>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Key strengths:</strong></p>
    <ul style="color:#333;line-height:1.8">
      <li>Excellent branded mobile app experience</li>
      <li>Clean, modern interface</li>
      <li>Good scheduling and membership management</li>
      <li>Strong onboarding and customer success support</li>
    </ul>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Considerations:</strong></p>
    <ul style="color:#333;line-height:1.8">
      <li>Not martial arts-specific; no belt or rank tracking</li>
      <li>Reporting features are adequate but not exceptional</li>
      <li>Pricing can be high for smaller schools</li>
      <li>Limited martial arts-specific integrations</li>
    </ul>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Pricing:</strong> Custom pricing, typically starting around $110/month. Requires consultation.</p>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Best for:</strong> Schools that prioritize a branded mobile experience and clean design over martial arts-specific features.</p>

    <h2 style="font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif">How to Make Your Decision</h2>

    <p style="color:#333">Choosing the right platform comes down to understanding your priorities. If you run a martial arts school and want software that was designed for exactly that purpose, platforms like Gripmode and Kicksite deserve the closest look. If you operate a multi-service facility, broader platforms like Mindbody or PushPress might be more appropriate, even though they require workarounds for martial arts-specific needs.</p>

    <p style="color:#333">Regardless of which platform you lean toward, take these steps before committing:</p>

    <ul style="color:#333;line-height:1.8">
      <li>Run a free trial and test it with real scenarios from your school</li>
      <li>Ask for references from other martial arts school owners on the platform</li>
      <li>Calculate total costs including processing fees, add-ons, and setup charges</li>
      <li>Understand the contract terms and cancellation policy</li>
      <li>Evaluate the migration support for moving from your current system</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 style="font-family:'Space Grotesk',sans-serif">What to Prioritize in Your Evaluation</h2>

    <p style="color:#333">With eight viable platforms on this list, narrowing down your choice can feel overwhelming. Focus on these three factors to cut through the noise:</p>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>First, industry fit.</strong> A platform built for martial arts will save you hours of workarounds compared to a general fitness platform that requires custom fields, manual belt tracking, and improvised solutions for program-based memberships. If martial arts is all you do, prioritize platforms that specialize in it.</p>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Second, total cost of ownership.</strong> Monthly subscription prices can be misleading. A platform advertising $99 per month with 3.5 percent processing fees and paid SMS add-ons may cost more than a platform charging $179 per month with lower processing fees and messaging included. Calculate your true annual cost based on your transaction volume and the features you actually need.</p>

    <p style="color:#333"><strong>Third, support quality.</strong> When your billing system goes down during a Saturday morning kids class, you need help now, not a ticket number and a promise to respond within 48 hours. Test each vendor's support responsiveness during your trial period by submitting a question and timing the response.</p>

    <p style="color:#333">The best software for your school is the one that fits your workflow, solves your biggest pain points, and grows with you as your school evolves. Take the time to choose carefully, and you will build your operations on a foundation that supports your growth for years to come.</p>

